Criticism is tough. We all receive it, because none of us are perfect. Even if we were, we would be condemned for being perfect. But Meditations highlights that it isn’t the criticism that makes us want to curl up in a ball and cry but rather our response to it, Criticism is usually met with either defence, anger or self-pity. Is this a resilient response? Marcus says no. We can choose to take criticism this way or we can assess the validity of the response and gain some perspective on someone’s opinion. And recall it is just that – someone’s opinion. We can choose to take the criticism under our belt and use it to better ourselves.  
</p>

<p>
