<p>

  

Basically, we have two boxes:, things we can control;, and things we cannot control. We should only be actively trying to maintain a lid on the first box as Aurelius suggests. What about the second box? Well, Meditations advises that box should be kept in a cupboard within our view so we are aware of it, but nothing should be done to
keep what’s inside of it contained, because it simply can’t be.
It is like stressing over a traffic light being red because we are running late to a meeting. Stress will not change the traffic light or make the driver in front of you drive the speed limit, it will only make us feel worse. It is a hard concept to put into practice, but it is being resilient to actively choose not to waste emotions and time on things we have no power over.Problems are created in the mind.

</p>

