<p>

This one is an expansion of the second theme we touched on. Meditations teaches that the mindset that created the problem cannot solve it. Success comes from mistakes whereas no success comes from an unwillingness to try due to fear of failure. The desire to try again even when things look bleak comes from a resilient mind, which Marcus Aurelius aided to leading a good life. 
</p>

<p>
If we fail a test and drop out of the subject due to fear of failing another test, we will ultimately never finish the course and never achieve what we set out to do in the first place. It is not the failed test that is stopping us, but rather the mindset we have taken onboard. Meditations teaches us that there is resilience in moving forwards, regardless of our situation. 
</p>

